                <h2>Essential Feeding Guidelines</h2>
                <p>Proper nutrition is the foundation of your dog's health and wellbeing. A balanced diet provides the energy and nutrients your dog needs to maintain a healthy weight, strong immune system, and optimal organ function.</p>
                
                <h3>Daily Feeding Requirements</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Adult Dogs:</strong> 2-3% of body weight in food daily</li>
                    <li><strong>Puppies:</strong> 3-4% of body weight, fed 3-4 times daily</li>
                    <li><strong>Senior Dogs:</strong> Adjusted portions based on activity level</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Key Nutrients</h3>
                <p>Dogs require a balanced mix of proteins, carbohydrates, fats, vitamins, and minerals:</p>
                
                <h4>Proteins (18-25%)</h4>
                <p>High-quality animal proteins should be the primary ingredient. Look for named meat sources like chicken, beef, fish, or lamb.</p>
                
                <h4>Fats (8-15%)</h4>
                <p>Essential for energy, coat health, and nutrient absorption. Omega-3 and omega-6 fatty acids are particularly important.</p>
                
                <h4>Carbohydrates</h4>
                <p>Provide energy and fiber. Good sources include sweet potatoes, brown rice, and vegetables.</p>
                
                <h2>Foods to Avoid</h2>
                <p>Never feed your dog these dangerous foods:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Chocolate</li>
                    <li>Grapes and raisins</li>
                    <li>Onions and garlic</li>
                    <li>Xylitol (artificial sweetener)</li>
                    <li>Avocado</li>
                    <li>Macadamia nuts</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h2>Feeding Schedule</h2>
                <p>Most adult dogs do well with two meals per day, spaced 8-12 hours apart. This helps with digestion and prevents overeating.</p>
